3.
arr = [1, 2, 3, 3]
 => [1, 2, 3, 3] 
[1, 2, 3, 3].uniq
 => [1, 2, 3] 
[1, 2, 3, 3].uniq!
 => [1, 2, 3] 

4. 
select documentation
Returns a new array containing all elements of ary for which the given block returns a true value.
If no block is given, an Enumerator is returned instead.
array = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]

select 
uses a boolean true or false to select the in the array elements to return, 
array.select {|e| e % 2 == 0}
=> [2, 4]

map documentation
Invokes the given block once for each element of self.
Creates a new array containing the values returned by the block.
If no block is given, an Enumerator is returned instead.

map 
can return a modified array
array.map { |e| e *2}
=> [2, 4, 6, 8, 10] 

